Introducing the @ayuga.in Kashmiri Saffron Gel Moisturizer with Jasmine. 

This breaks down into a water like texture and gets absorbed into the skin instantly. And to top it off, it is cooling too. I didn’t expect this to be cooling too but it feels amazing, especially on a humid gloomy monsoon day. 

Constant sweating during the humid monsoon days means dehydrated skin. And where most moisturizers make our skin feel slightly oily/sticky in the humidity, what we need is a water-light gel moisturizer that absorbs instantly that does not make your
skin feel sticky this monsoon. 

Made with Kashmiri Saffron, sourced directly from Pampore region in Kashmir, this moisturizer is Made Safe Certified and Dermatologically tested to be gentle on the skin. Its non-sticky, water-light formula makes your skin glow from within. Enriched with Niacinamide, Vitamin C, Allantoin & Witch Hazel- this soothes the skin, evens out skin tone and gives you a golden glow.

🛒Get yours now from @ayuga.in ✨

Here’s my secret solution for hair loss! Rosemary ✨

Skip the hassle of DIY rosemary with @mamaearth.in Rosemary Leave in Hair Serum. 

It is the perfect combination of household DIY’s. It has 95% Pure Rosemary Extract, Anagain. 

An oil should be left on before washing hair and used for conditioning purposes. It helps reduce hair fall. Whereas a leave in serum, which is usually more effective can be used post hair wash and even on a daily basis. It helps with new hair growth as well as reducing hair fall.

Rosemary : Stimulates Hair Growth
Methi Dana : Controls Hair Fall
Anagain : Thicker and denser Hair 

With the perfect combination of these highly effective ingredients, this product is an absolute necessity for people like me who want a product that works but do not enjoy the thick and heavy feeling of oil on the scalp. And to top it off, we do need to stand in the kitchen for hours to make your rosemary DIYs now. 

Just order your Rosemary hair growth scalp serum from MamaEarth.in and use code MAMAIG20 to get added discounts.
